From George Pandelios Subject Re IDE Low Level Format In article xiangxin shen writes In article Hector Mandel writes I accidentally tried to low level format my Western Digital Caviar Is there a public domain or shareware utility available that will allow me to fix it I am no expert on But I am pretty sure there is no way to recover IDE drive has mapping information written directly on When you low level format it the information itself is gone as well I don't think you can get it back unless you send it back to Western Digital and ask them to refurbish it for Jim Well I have a different story to I attempted to low level format a WD disk about a year When I understood my error I contacted They told me that I hadn't hurt the drive and that I should just run FDISK and FORMAT S on It was Also I understand that Western Digital's BBS may have some low level formatting routines specifically available for IDE You probably need to talk to them and get the straight George George Pandelios Internet Software Engineering Institute usenet sei gjp Fifth Avenue Voice Pittsburgh PA FAX Disclaimer These opinions are my own and do not reflect those of the Software Engineering Institute its sponsors customers clients affiliates or Carnegie Mellon In fact any resemblence of these opinions to any individual living or dead fictional or real is purely So